00:43:08.140 --> 00:43:11.410
Not a minute's worth of
environmental releasers.

00:43:11.410 --> 00:43:15.620
But instead general
pictures of what environment

00:43:15.620 --> 00:43:17.010
has to do with aggression.

00:43:17.010 --> 00:43:21.019
Some of the broad theories that
have come out over the years.

00:43:21.019 --> 00:43:22.810
Let's take a five minute
break before that.

00:43:26.120 --> 00:43:28.580
To quickly go through
this deal again.

00:43:28.580 --> 00:43:32.005
So you've got amino
acid precursor.

00:43:32.005 --> 00:43:36.160
Tryptophan, that's your building
block for making serotonin.

00:43:36.160 --> 00:43:39.610
Key enzyme coded for by a gene.

00:43:39.610 --> 00:43:40.690
It's a protein.

00:43:40.690 --> 00:43:43.410
Key enzyme that turns
it into the first step.

00:43:43.410 --> 00:43:44.404
And then this enzyme.

00:43:44.404 --> 00:43:45.570
There's always a ton around.

00:43:45.570 --> 00:43:48.140
It automatically gets
turned into serotonin.

00:43:48.140 --> 00:43:49.750
So now you have serotonin.

00:43:49.750 --> 00:43:53.700
Serotonin will do its thing
by way of binding to serotonin

00:43:53.700 --> 00:43:54.720
receptors.

00:43:54.720 --> 00:43:57.730
And at some point serotonin
tone will be broken down

00:43:57.730 --> 00:43:59.870
into this waste product.

00:43:59.870 --> 00:44:02.680
So a gene coding
for this protein,

00:44:02.680 --> 00:44:05.970
a gene coding for this one,
which we're not interested in.

00:44:05.970 --> 00:44:09.150
A bunch of genes coding
for the receptors.

00:44:09.150 --> 00:44:11.880
And genes coding for
these two enzymes.

00:44:11.880 --> 00:44:13.860
And the whole point
there being that there's

00:44:13.860 --> 00:44:16.540
different versions
of these genes

00:44:16.540 --> 00:44:20.290
for the synthetic enzymes,
for the degradative enzymes,

00:44:20.290 --> 00:44:21.560
for the receptors.

00:44:21.560 --> 00:44:24.250
And thus beginning to
look at whether that

00:44:24.250 --> 00:44:28.120
predicts differences in
levels of aggressive behavior.

00:44:28.120 --> 00:44:30.340
So that's what that was about.

00:44:30.340 --> 00:44:33.950
In addition, was just told
a great story about somebody

00:44:33.950 --> 00:44:37.090
who was under tremendous
duress to supply

00:44:37.090 --> 00:44:40.700
alcohol for her younger
16-year-old sister

00:44:40.700 --> 00:44:44.330
and friends at a sweet
16 party and decided,

00:44:44.330 --> 00:44:46.010
no way is this happening.

00:44:46.010 --> 00:44:49.170
And thus bought a bunch of
bottles of something or other

00:44:49.170 --> 00:44:51.890
and took the labels off
and put other labels on.

00:44:51.890 --> 00:44:53.960
And before you knew it,
